Sign up here to get Inside the Jets delivered to your inbox each Wednesday morning. If you were discussing the future of the Jets at this time last year, one name sure to have been mentioned as part of the long-term core was Mekhi Becton. The mammoth left tackle was coming off an impressive rookie year in which he dominated at times. The talk last offseason was of him being a perennial All-Pro, the kind of player who  looked like he would be a fixture with the team for the next decade. That feels like a long time ago.